Bafana Bafana’s opponents for the 2022 group stage World Cup Qualifiers have been revealed. In the draw that took place in Cairo, Egypt on Tuesday night, Bafana were drawn in a tough Group G alongside Ghana, Zimbabwe and Ethiopia. Molefi Ntseki’s charges will be looking to book a spot at the World Cup after missing out on the last two editions in Brazil and Russia. The last time they appeared at the biggest stage was back in 2010 when they hosted the tournament. The qualifiers will commence in March with only the group winners set to advance to the final round of qualifiers.  CAF African World Cup qualifiers Groups Group A: Algeria, Burkina Faso, Niger, Djibouti Group B: Tunisia, Zambia, Mauritania, Equatorial Guinea Group C: Nigeria, Cape Verde, Central African Republic, Liberia Group D: Cameroon, Ivory Coast, Mozambique, Malawi Group E: Mali, Uganda, Kenya, RwandaGroup F: Egypt, Gabon, Libya, Angola Group G: Ghana, South Africa, Zimbabwe, Ethiopia Group H: Senegal, Congo, Namibia, Togo Group I: Morocco, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Sudan Group J: DR Congo, Benin, Madagascar, Tanzania 